                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="18514" author="memelet" created="Tue, 11 Jul 2006 02:07:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On second thought, onSetup/TeardownBeforeNonTransaction() is not such a good name. What I am looking is a setup hook which always runs, regardless of whether the test method is transactional or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23427" author="memelet" created="Wed, 25 Apr 2007 07:28:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any chance of getting this in the road map?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the fixes+ &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;changed the visibility of AbstractDependencyInjectionSpringContextTests&apos;s &quot;injectDependencies&quot; method to protected&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;changed the visibility of AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests&apos;s &quot;transactionDefinition&quot; field to protected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This all that is forcing us to have a custom version of AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23440" author="memelet" created="Wed, 25 Apr 2007 23:41:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Juergen!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23488" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 29 Apr 2007 06:19:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After some consideration, I&apos;ve decided to simply turn &quot;onSetUp()&quot; and &quot;onTearDown()&quot; non-final. This allows for overriding these methods, implementing common setup/teardown behavior that executes in any case, either before or after the standard setup/teardown code (with those overridden methods calling the respective super method appropriately). This is also consistent with other changes that we recently did in the general test class hierarchy, relaxing the visibility and &apos;final&apos; restrictions for more flexible overriding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This change should be available in the next 2.0.5 snapshot (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/snapshots&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/snapshots&lt;/a&gt;). Please give it a try and let us know whether it works for you!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23548" author="memelet" created="Tue, 1 May 2007 23:46:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Perfect! Wtih this and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2479&quot; title=&quot;AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests subclasses should have access to transactionDefinition&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2479&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2479&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I have finally deleted my hacked up AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
